Minnesota Lynx head coach Cheryl Reeve reacts against the Indiana Fever in the first half of Game 5 of the WNBA basketball finals, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015, in Minneapolis. (AP Photo/Jim Mone) Posted: Wednesday, October 14, 2015 10:14 pm Lynx capture 3rd title in 5 years with 69-52 win in Game 5 Associated Press | 0 comments 
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) — Sylvia Fowles had 20 points and 11 rebounds, and the Minnesota Lynx captured their third championship in five years with a 69-52 victory over the Indiana Fever in Game 5 of the WNBA Finals on Wednesday night. 
Seimone Augustus added 16 points and Rebekkah Brunson grabbed 14 rebounds for the Lynx, who also won it all in 2011 and 2013.
